250 g Ground Beef
¾ cup Jasmine Rice
¼ cup Basil Pesto
56 g Yellow Onion, chopped
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
113 g Baby Tomatoes
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
2 tbsp Balsamic Glaze
56 g Baby Spinach
2 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
1 tbsp Oil*

Add rice to the boiling water. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 12-14 min. Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Roughly chop spinach
Carefully poke tomatoes with a fork or with the tip of a knife.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then tomatoes. Cook, stirring occasionally, until burst, 3-4 min.
Transfer tomatoes to a medium bowl. Drizzle half the balsamic glaze (All for 4ppl) over top. Season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat. Set aside.

Re-heat the large non-stick pan over medium-high
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then beef and onions.
Cook, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.** Season with salt and pepper.
Add pesto and garlic puree. Cook stirring often until coated, 1 min.

Fluff rice with a fork. Add spinach and 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) butter. Season with salt, then stir to combine.
Divide rice between bowls, then top with beef and blistered tomatoes.
Sprinkle Parmesan over top.

If you've opted to get beef, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the turkey.**